<problem>

<p>How many solutions can you find to the equation <m>x + y + z = 20</m>,  where <m>x, y</m>, and <m>z</m> are positive integers ?</p>
  
<p>Note that <m>x = 1,\; y = 1,\; z = 18</m> and <m>x = 18,\; y = 1,\; z = 1</m> are different solutions. Also, <m>0</m> is not a positive integer.</p>


<!--*********************************************
            User solution input
**********************************************-->

<p>Number of solutions =  
  <answer name="ans1">171</answer>
</p>

